<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Tesla</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tesla Inc. is an electric car company,=
 but arguably its most important mission is generating cash for Elon Musk. =
This is not just me saying that. In 2017, Musk=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35069108.286345/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZ=
XJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMzEvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWlzLW92ZXJwYWlk=
P2NtcGlkPUJCRDA0MTcyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1=
uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDQxNyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cB6d5b2f6d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;">told a Tesla director</a> that he neede=
d billions of dollars=C2=A0from Tesla =E2=80=9Cso that I can put as much as=
 possible towards minimizing existential risk by putting the money towards =
Mars.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CColonizing Mars is an expensive endeavor,=E2=80=9D =
a Delaware Chancery Court judge <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/35069108.286345/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bWVudHMvd=
XNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3JwYU9FZWZRc2UwMC92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB21ed=
620e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;">wrote this year</a>.=C2=A0=E2=80=9CMusk believes he has a mor=
al obligation to direct his wealth toward that goal,=C2=A0and Musk views hi=
s compensation from Tesla as a means of bankrolling that mission.=E2=80=9D =
Maybe Mars was more of a 2017 thing, and in 2024 Musk has competing priorit=
ies (artificial intelligence, brain implants, Twitter), but the point is:</=
p><ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Elon Musk has big plans for the world,=
 and a sense of moral mission in pursuing them.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-=
bottom: 5px;">Those plans require a lot of capital.</li>=09<li style=3D"mar=
gin-bottom: 5px;">Except Tesla (now), which is a public company with about =
$500 billion worth of liquid public stock, and which he can use for the oth=
er stuff.</li></ul><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I do not want to suggest th=
at Tesla is purely Elon Musk=E2=80=99s personal piggybank, because that=E2=
=80=99s not true. It makes electric cars.=C2=A0It continues to invest in ne=
w projects. It has, historically, generated a whole lot of value for Tesla =
shareholders=C2=A0<em>other=C2=A0</em>than Elon Musk, though not as much re=
cently. (It has lost more than 60% of its value since the peak in 2021.) Bu=
t Telsa is=C2=A0<em>also=C2=A0</em>Musk=E2=80=99s main piggybank, and he ha=
s a lot of needs. Musk went and solved the (difficult, capital-intensive) p=
roblem of electric cars, and now Tesla is his main source of wealth for sol=
ving the many other difficult, capital-intensive problems that interest him=
.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You know the story: In 2018, to satisfy M=
usk=E2=80=99s Mars ambitions, Tesla=E2=80=99s board granted him a package o=
f conditional Tesla stock options that would be worth something like $55 bi=
llion if Tesla succeeded wildly. It did: By 2021 Tesla was worth $1.2 trill=
ion, Musk got=C2=A0all the options, and for a time they were worth more tha=
n $100 billion. He used his vast Tesla wealth =E2=80=94=C2=A0selling shares=
 and borrowing against them<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !importa=
nt; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0to fund his various other projects, like buying Tw=
itter and also I am sure something Mars-related. By this year, he was back =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35069108.286345/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMTYvbW9yZ=
2FuLXN0YW5sZXktbGVha2VkLXNvbWUtYmxvY2stdHJhZGVzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA0MTcyNF9NT05F=
WVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI=
0MDQxNyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdee506c3" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"c=
olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;">asking Tesla=E2=80=99s board for more money</a>. But meanwhile a di=
sgruntled Tesla shareholder named Richard Tornetta had sued the company, ar=
guing that Musk=E2=80=99s pay package was illegal, and in January that Dela=
ware judge <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3506910=
8.286345/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMD=
EtMzEvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWlzLW92ZXJwYWlkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA0MTcyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0b=
V9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDQxNyZ1dG1f=
Y2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC6d5b2f6d" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">ruled=
 that it was</a>. And so Musk=E2=80=99s options disappeared, arguably makin=
g at least a theoretical dent in his ability to do Mars, AI, brains, tweets=
 or whatever it is he=E2=80=99s up to now.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
Today Tesla <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/350691=
08.286345/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvM=
DAwMTMxODYwNS8wMDAxMTA0NjU5MjQwNDgwNDAvdG0yMzI2MDc2ZDEzX3ByZTE0YS5odG0/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cBad4711e3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">filed a proxy statement</a> for its =
2024 annual meeting, asking shareholders to fix that problem and turn the m=
oney faucet back on. There are two specific asks:</p><ol style=3D"list-styl=
e-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margi=
n-bottom: 5px;">That Delaware judge ruled that Musk=E2=80=99s 2018=C2=A0pay=
 package was illegal in part because she found problems with the shareholde=
r vote approving it. So Tesla is asking the shareholders to approve the 201=
8=C2=A0pay package again, so Musk can get his options back.</li>=09<li styl=
e=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It was a=C2=A0<em>Delaware=C2=A0</em>judge who ru=
led that Musk=E2=80=99s pay package was illegal, because Tesla, like most b=
ig US public companies, is incorporated in Delaware. Presumably a=C2=A0<em>=
Texas=C2=A0</em>judge wouldn=E2=80=99t do that, since Texas apparently love=
s Musk as a matter of state policy. So Tesla is asking the shareholders to =
approve reincorporating the company in Texas.=C2=A0</li></ol><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">Each of these raises some complications.</p><p style=3D"marg=
in: 16px 0;">First, the economics of re-approving the 2018 pay package. In =
2018, Tesla=E2=80=99s board granted Musk 12 tranches of stock options, each=
 representing 1% of Tesla=E2=80=99s stock at the time. The tranches would v=
est based on performance targets, particularly market capitalization target=
s: The first tranche vested if Tesla hit a $100 billion market cap (up from=
 about $59 billion at the time of the grant), and the other 11 tranches wou=
ld vest at $50 billion increments, up to $650 billion for the final tranche=
.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: tran=
sparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0He had 10 years to hit those milestones; he hit them in three. <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35069108.286345/aHR0=
cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMDAwMTMxODYwNS8=
wMDAxMTA0NjU5MjQwNDgwNDAvdG0yMzI2MDc2ZDEzX3ByZTE0YS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
